to see output of a pod:
$ k logs <pod-name>

in job-definition.yaml:
the value of spec.completions is specifying how many pods will be created successfully, it will be done one by one which means that the 2nd pod should be created 
when 1st is completed, also if the 1st is failed, it will create 2nd one, and keep doing in this way until 3 of them successfully complete if we specify it 3.

spec.parallelism is creating pod at the same time, if any failed it will keep creating until 3 of them complete if it's specified as 3.


